       The default input focus policy is an "explicit" selection
       policy; the user must perform a mouse button action or a key
       action to change the input focus.  A "track pointer" policy,
       which changes the input focus to match the pointer's posi-
       tion (no other action is required), is also available.        |
       These policies are explained further in Chapter 13.

