       As an application programmer, you have several ways to con-
       trol a user's ability to resize your client window:

          +o A window cannot be resized smaller than the minimum
            size specified by your client.

          +o A window cannot be resized smaller than the minimum
            size dictated by the components you select for the win-
            dow frame.

          +o A window cannot be resized larger than the maximum win-
            dow size specified by your client.

          +o A client can indicate that the resize function should
            not apply (use the _MOTIF_WM_HINTS property, Chapter     |
            12).

       Window frames can be configured to omit resize handles.  The  |
       frame can then be configured to have a border or to be bord-
       erless.






